<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-17T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-17T04:00:00-05:00" n="213" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Mutual Guarantee (Locarno)/460:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-17T10:00:00+01:00">March 17,
                                    1936—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>11. In conversation with Prime Minister he stated that while appreciating
                            extreme gravity of European situation he is optimistic of eventual
                            peaceful solution. Nevertheless in case of failure Yugoslavia like other
                            Little and Balkan Entente countries must give France full and
                            unqualified support. Yugoslav economic life has been seriously disrupted
                            by sanctions against Italy which were adopted most reluctantly and
                            Government is therefore greatly alarmed and opposed to possibility of
                            being forced to adopt similar action against Germany its next most
                            important customer with which its profitable commercial relations have
                            been showing constant improvement.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>